Sentencas: The performance of yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ)-samaria-doped ceria (SDC) dual layer electrolyte anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (AS-SOFC) was investigated.
Titulo: Performance Investigation of Dual Layer Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia-Samaria-Doped Ceria Electrolyte for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Tape-casting, lamination, and co-sintering of the NiO-YSZ anode followed by wet powder spraying of the SDC buffer layer and BSCF cathode was proposed for fabrication of these cells as an effective means of reducing the number of sintering stages required.
Titulo: Performance Investigation of Dual Layer Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia-Samaria-Doped Ceria Electrolyte for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The AS-SOFC showed a significant fuel cell performance of similar to 1.9W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Performance Investigation of Dual Layer Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia-Samaria-Doped Ceria Electrolyte for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The fuel cell performance varies significantly with the sintering temperature of the SDC buffer layer.
Titulo: Performance Investigation of Dual Layer Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia-Samaria-Doped Ceria Electrolyte for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: An optimal buffer layer sintering temperature of 1350 degrees C occurs due to a balance between the YSZ-SDC contact and densification at low sintering temperature and reactions between YSZ and SDC at high sintering temperatures.
Titulo: Performance Investigation of Dual Layer Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia-Samaria-Doped Ceria Electrolyte for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: At high sintering temperatures, the reactions between YSZ and SDC have a detrimental effect on the fuel cell performance resulting in no power at a sintering temperature of 1500 degrees C.
Titulo: Performance Investigation of Dual Layer Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia-Samaria-Doped Ceria Electrolyte for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
